narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learnt a LOT in this course  it was very content heavy but definitely provided me with a great foundation moving forward in STEM.
We learned a lot of the basics of biochem, transcription, etc.
Intro biology content (cell bio and biochemistry)

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Overall, the course was great! However, my engagement was definitely higher for the first half than the second half. A major part of this probably has to do with the enrichment packets we received in the first half of the course. They allowed us to reflect on the content we learnt and easily identify our strengths and weaknesses. On the other hand, we didn't really receive any enrichment packets for the second half, and with the content being a bit more complex and lectures having less structure in comparison to the first half of the course, I struggled with keeping up with the content. I also think having a TA for this course would be very helpful, since although we were able to collaborate together as a class, we sometimes reached dead ends.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! This course is a must-have for any STEM student, but it also taught me a lot about the basics of biology. I haven't studied biology in a while, so it felt really nice getting to learn new biology topics here at Yale!
I would recommend taking it if you need it, but also after taking the intro chem sequence. Some things make more sense that way.

narratives.question_text: The Canvas course site allowed me to identify and access required course materials easily.

comments: We covered a lot of content which will most definitely come up in my future STEM classes!
